  Locus:
    Page: 258
    Verse: 6
Tags:
  - Hypocrisy
---
Hypocrisy is pretending to be perfect, and in the process, imposing a sense
of judgement and guilt on those around you. Hypocrisy is giving everybody
the verbal assurance that you are living up to your own standards, when you
are really not.
